# Project: Photo Gallery

Galleries are the perfect grid exercise: a responsive layout, a featured tile that spans, hover
overlays using positioning, and `object-cover` to keep images tidy.

<ProjectBrief
	title="Build a responsive photo gallery"
	time="35 min"
	goal="Create an auto-responsive image grid where the first photo spans two columns, images keep their aspect with object-cover, and each tile reveals a caption overlay on hover."
	requirements={[
		'A grid that reflows column count by available width',
		'A featured first tile spanning 2 columns',
		'Images cropped cleanly with object-cover and a fixed aspect',
		'A caption overlay positioned over each image on hover'
	]}
	stretch={[
		'Add rounded corners and a subtle zoom on hover',
		'Make the overlay gradient instead of flat',
		'Add a small icon button in each tile corner'
	]}
/>

## The finished gallery

<CodeBlock
	playground
	filename="gallery.html (solution)"
	code={`<div class="grid grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(10rem,1fr))] gap-3">
  <figure class="group relative col-span-2 overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
    <img src="https://picsum.photos/id/1015/600/400" alt="" class="aspect-video w-full object-cover transition duration-300 group-hover:scale-105" />
    <figcaption class="absolute inset-x-0 bottom-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-black/70 to-transparent p-3 text-sm font-medium text-white opacity-0 transition group-hover:opacity-100">
      Featured · Mountain lake
    </figcaption>
  </figure>
  <figure class="group relative overflow-hidden rounded-xl">
